President Uhuru Kenyatta has asked police to expedite investigations into the killing of Kenyan athlete Agnes Tirop. Tirop, who was part of Team Kenya at the Olympics Games in Tokyo in 2021, was found dead with stab wounds on October 13, 2021, at her home in Iten, Elgeyo Marakwet County. President Kenyatta described her as a Kenyan hero and champion.           Tirop's decorated performances include a World Cross Country title in 2015. Tirop set the new world record in the 10km road race after clocking 30:01 during the Adizero Road to Records event in Herzogenaurach, Germany on September 12, 2021. Bahrain's Kalkidan Gezahegne then lowered that record during the Giants Geneva 10km in Geneva, Switzerland, setting a new world record in 29:38 in a race in whihc Tirop was second.